      "content": "That deafening silence is the sound of a profound loss, and it's exhausting to carry that weight every single day. When the emptiness feels permanent, sometimes the smallest act of self-care can feel like a monumental effort. Even if it doesn't fix the emptiness, finding one small thing that offers a flicker of peace—a quiet walk, a specific song—can offer a momentary reprieve from the fight. Please consider reaching out to a crisis line; they are equipped to sit in that quiet with you.",
      "source": "target",
